This survived filtering because BeautifulSoup converted `attributeName` to lowercase and the filter only removes `on*` attributes from tags, not attribute values. Whether this triggers an alert depends on browser implementation of SVG SMIL animations.

The test script expects the file at `/app/out.html` to trigger an alert AFTER the filter processes it. The filter uses `/tests/filter.py` path which doesn't exist in this environment, which is why my manual verification used `/app/filter.py`.

